The following is a '''list of [[ecoregion]]s in [[Costa Rica]]'''. An ecoregion is an ecologically and geographically defined area that is smaller than a [[bioregion]], which in turn is smaller than an [[ecozone]]. All three of these are larger than an [[ecosystem]]. Ecoregions cover relatively large areas of land or water, and contain characteristic, geographically distinct assemblages of natural communities and species. The biodiversity of flora, fauna and ecosystems that characterise an ecoregion tends to be distinct from that of other ecoregions. Costa Rica is a country in Central America, bordered by [[Nicaragua]] to the north, [[Panama]] to the southeast, the [[Pacific Ocean]] to the west, and the [[Caribbean Sea]] to the east. It contains 5% of the world's [[biodiversity]].{{citation needed|date=September 2013}}
==Terrestrial ecoregions== The following [[terrestrial ecoregion]]s have been identified in Costa Rica:<ref name=WWF2000>{{cite book|editor1=Bermúdez M., Mariela |editor2=Joaquín Sánchez G. |title=Identificación de vacíos de información botánica en Centroamérica |year=2000 |publisher=WWF Centroamérica, Museo Nacional de Costa Rica, Red de Herbarios de Mesoamérica y el Caribe |page=17 |url=http://wwf.panda.org/?133202/Identificacion-de-Vacios-de-Informacion-Botanica-en-Centroamerica |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>[http://www.inbio.ac.cr/osa/paginas/definicion-carac.html Programa de monitoreo ecológico del área de conservación Osa, Costa Rica. El sitio Osa: definición y caracterización.] PROMEC-ACOSA. (in Spanish)</ref> *[[Neotropic]] [[tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests]] **[[Central American Atlantic moist forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Central American Atlantic moist forests|url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0111|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> **[[Cocos Island moist forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Cocos Island moist forests |url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0116|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> **[[Costa Rican seasonal moist forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Costa Rican seasonal moist forests |url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0119|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> **[[Isthmian-Atlantic moist forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Isthmian-Atlantic moist forests |url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0129|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> **[[Isthmian-Pacific moist forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Isthmian-Pacific moist forests |url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0130|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> **[[Talamancan montane forests]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Talamancan montane forests |url=http://worldwildlife.org/ecoregions/nt0167|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref> *[[Neotropic