k-nuclear-reactor-uranium-facility-bankruptcy-newyork.htm|title=Kodak Nuclear Reactor Containing Uranium Housed In New York Facility For Over 30 Years|author=Nadine DeNinno|date=14 May 2012|website=International Business Times|accessdate=20 August 2015}}</ref><ref>http://www.democratandchronicle.com/assets/pdf/A2189207511.pdf</ref> || [[Rochester, New York]] || Californium Neutron Flux Multiplier || 5.8&nbsp;W || 1975 - 2006 |- | [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] || [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]] || Tank Type HWR Reflected ([[MIT Nuclear Research Reactor|MITR-II]]) || 6 MW || 1958 - |- | [[Missouri University of Science and Technology]] || [[Rolla, Missouri]] || Pool ([[Missouri University of Science and Technology Nuclear Reactor|MSTR]]) || 200&nbsp;kW || 1961 - |- | [[National Institute of Standards and Technology]] || [[Gaithersburg, Maryland]] || Tank Type, Heavy Water Moderated || 20 MW || 1967 - |- | [[North Carolina State University]] || [[Raleigh, North Carolina]] || [[Pulstar (nuclear reactor)|Pulstar]] || 1 MW || 1973 - |- | [[Ohio State University]] || [[Columbus, Ohio]] || Pool (modified Lockheed) [http://reactor.osu.edu/home] || 500&nbsp;kW || 1961 - |- | [[Oregon State University]] || [[Corvallis, Oregon]] || [[TRIGA]] Mark II ([[OSU Radiation Center|OSTR]]) || 1.1 MW || 1967 - |- | [[Penn State University]] || [[University Park, Pennsylvania]] || [[TRIGA]] [[Pennsylvania State University Radiation Science & Engineering Center|BNR]] Reactor || 1.1 MW || 1955 - |- | [[Purdue University]] || [[West Lafayette, Indiana]] || Lockheed ([[Purdue University Reactor Number One|PUR-1]]) || 1&nbsp;kW || 1962 - |- | [[Reed College]] || [[Portland, Oregon]] || [[TRIGA]] Mark I ([[Reed Reactor Facility|RRR]]) || 250&nbsp;kW || 1968 - |- | [[Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute]] || [[Schenectady, New York]] || Reactor Critical Facility<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.osti.gov/geothermal/servlets/purl/505687-xPA1Ut/webviewable/505687.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessd