==Uruguay== {{Main|Nuclear energy in Uruguay}}
*URR reactor - A small pool-type research reactor placed in Centro de Investigaciones Nucleares (CIN). In operation since the early 1970s up until 1997 when it was dismantled and returned to United States<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lr21.com.uy/tecnologia/1001186-uruguay-reabre-el-debate-luego-de-la-tragedia-en-japon|title=Uruguay reabre el debate luego de la tragedia en Japón|publisher=LaRed21|date=31 October 2011|accessdate=6 November 2013|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lr21.com.uy/politica/340143-uruguay-tuvo-un-reactor|title=Uruguay tuvo un reactor|publisher=LaRed21|language=Spanish|date=17 November 2008|accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref> due to a 1997 law against use of nuclear energy in Uruguay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espectador.com/1v4_contenido.php?id=117430&sts=1|title=Las bases para un debate sobre la energía nuclear|publisher=El espectador|date=17 March 2008|accessdate=6 November 2013|language=Spanish|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131106204238/http://www.espectador.com/1v4_contenido.php?id=117430&sts=1|archivedate=6 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
