{{short description|The average of all the high water heights observed over a period of several years}}
{{Redirect|MHW}}
'''Mean High Water''' ('''MHW''') is the [[average]] of all the [[Tide|high water height]]s observed over a period of several years.  For example, in the United States this period spans 19 years and is referred to as the [[National Tidal Datum Epoch]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov/datum_options.html |title=Tidal Datums |publisher=tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov }}</ref>

