{{Infobox organization |name = Renewable Energy Research Centre |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1986 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [https://univdhaka.academia.edu/Departments/Renewable_Energy_Research_Centre Renewable Energy Research Centre] |remarks = }}
'''Renewable Energy Research Centre''' is an autonomous national research institute, under the University of Dhaka, that carries out research and plans water resource management projects in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="rerc">{{cite web|last1=Khan|first1=Md Kamrul Alam|title=Renewable Energy Research Centre|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Renewable_Energy_Research_Centre|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=1 January 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Easy loan proposed for self-financed renewable energy projects|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-94943|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=30 June 2009|language=en}}</ref> It has a particular focus on solar energy and works with the Bangladesh Solar Energy Society.<ref>{{cite news|title=Focus more on renewable energy: analysts|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-245833|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=12 August 2012|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Generation of 3000MW renewable energy possible by 2020'|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-80953|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=23 March 2009|language=en}}</ref>
==History== Renewable Energy Research Centre was established in 1986 under the Faculty of Science of the [[University of Dhaka]]. It is managed by an advisory board that is chaired by the Vice-Chancellor of University of Dhaka. It specialises on solar energy research and provides MSc, MPhil, and PhD degrees.<ref name="rerc"></ref> The centre opened an energy park in 1988 on its premises.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hasan|first1=Imrul|title=Renewable Energy Research Centre|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2006/03/20/d603202505128.htm|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=archive.thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star}}</ref> In 2008 a 1.1kW rooftop solar grid was installed in the research centre with the financial support of the [[Ministry of Science and Technology (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Science and Technology]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Grid-connected solar power shines at DU campus|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-60011|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=The Daily Star|date=24 October 2008|language=en}}</ref> Renewable Energy Resource Assessment is a project under the Renewable Energy Research Centre and is a project of [[United Nations Environment Programme]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Harness renewable energy|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2003/12/29/d31229060364.htm|accessdate=1 January 2018|work=archive.thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star}}</ref>
